            <property name="text" class="ptolemy.kernel.util.StringAttribute" value="This transformation rule flattens hierarchy in a model. A level of hierarchy is&#10;created with a composite actor. The pattern of this rule matches the composite&#10;actor and the replacement, which is empty, means to remove the composite&#10;actor as a wrapper.&#10;&#10;Note that the removal only affects the hierarchy wrapper, and the content within&#10;the composite actor, which is removed, remains and is automatically moved to&#10;the higher level. Connections between the content inside the composite actor&#10;and other actors at the higher level are made automatically.&#10;&#10;To remove a composite actor together with its content, in which case the&#10;composite actor is considered a blackbox, an AtomicActorMatcher should be&#10;used instead (with a subclass criterion with value&#10;&quot;ptolemy.actor.CompositeActor&quot;).&#10;&#10;Created by Thomas Huining Feng">
